{
  "texts": [
    "The importance of this factor lies in its ability to enhance overall energy yield by maintaining optimal operating conditions.",
    "The orientation of solar panels, whether facing north-south or east-west, significantly influences the amount of sunlight received and, consequently, solar cell temperature (Atsu et al., 2020).",
    "The direction in which panels are oriented determines their exposure to direct sunlight.",
    "System planners must strategically decide the orientation based on the solar path and prevailing climate conditions.",
    "Optimizing panel orientation is a key aspect of thermal management, ensuring that solar cells receive sunlight effectively without being subjected to excessive heating."
  ]
}